ST FRANCIS BAY – Swift action by members of the South African Police Service (SAPS) in St Francis Bay led to the arrest of a 24-year-old man within four hours of a murder at the town, Eastern Cape police said on Saturday. It was alleged that the 25-year-old victim and friends were chatting in Tarragona Road, Sea Vista, in St Francis Bay on Friday, police said in a statement. READ: Dundee man sentenced to 30 years in jail for murder by KZN court “According to information, the 24-year-old male suspect approached the victim at about [3.30pm]. The 24-year-old suspect suddenly pulled out a knife and stabbed the victim in his chest. He died on the scene and the suspect fled into the bushes.” Police were summoned to the scene and a comprehensive search of the area followed. At about 7.30pm the suspect was apprehended in Sea Vista and the alleged murder weapon was also seized. Humansdorp policing cluster acting commander Colonel Simon Swarts expressed heartfelt condolences to the family of the victim, and commended the police officers for their swift action that resulted in the arrest of the suspect. The man was due to appear in the Humansdorp Magistrate’s Court on Monday on a charge of murder. African News Agency